HcRule.recommendedAction: Check availabilityStatus attribute for more details and observe Alarms for failure indication. Resolve the problem that caused the resource to be inoperable. Remote actions: 1. Check the configuration of the NbapCommon MO instance. For information on configuration, see Manage Radio Network WCDMA. 2. Perform a ping command towards affected RNC node. Check for available MO Router and MO NextHop (address) on NearEnd and MO IpAccessHostEt (ipAddress) created for Iub on FarEnd (RNC). Based on it create a ping command to next hop, then to FarEnd. Example: mcc router=traffic ping --count 3 --packetsize 1000 x.x.x.x. In case of unsuccessful ping, check if the node configuration matches the required IP design. Contact the transmission department to check the availability of IP network. 3. Check status of the connection in the related RNC node. On-site actions: 1. Validate cabling and port connectivity for Iub transport connection.
